text.tspan: Microwave radiometer sensitive to atmospheric temperature and humidity,
used on US satellites NOAA-16 (1998 launch), NOAA-17 (2000) and NOAA-
18 (2002). Engineering model on display is a prototype used as a flight
spare on NOAA-17. All flight instruments on AMSU-B were procured and
tested by the Met Office and supplied to NOAA. Data from AMSU-B is used by
the Met Office in operational forecasting models.
